# Cursor Rules for Simple UI

## General Behavior
*   Always use TypeScript.
*   Prefer functional components with named exports.
*   Use "use client" directive for any component using hooks or event listeners.

## Design Density
*   Default to **compact density**. This is a product-oriented system, not marketing.
*   Control heights: `h-8` (32px) default. Never `h-10`+ for default controls.
*   Container padding: `p-3` to `p-4`. Never `p-6` or larger.
*   Body text: `text-sm` (14px). Use `text-xs` for labels, metadata, help text.
*   Headings: Max `text-2xl` for h1. No `text-4xl` or larger in product views.
*   Border radius (concentric logic):
    *   Page/floating surfaces (Card, Dialog, Select dropdown, Popover): `rounded-xl`.
    *   Inline controls (Button, Input, Textarea, inner menu items): `rounded-lg`.
    *   Small elements (Checkbox, resize handle): `rounded-sm`.
    *   Pill elements (Badge, Chip, Switch, Progress): `rounded-full`.
*   Shadows (3-tier scale):
    *   Grounded surfaces (Card, Alert): `shadow-sm`.
    *   Floating surfaces (Popover, Select, HoverCard, Tooltip): `shadow-md`.
    *   Prominent overlays (Dialog, Sheet, Drawer): `shadow-lg`.

## Import Patterns
*   Import UI components from `@acme/ui/[component]`.
*   Import icons from `lucide-react`.
*   Import motion from `framer-motion`.

## Styling Rules
*   Use `cn()` for class merging.
*   Use `cva()` for variant definitions.
*   Do NOT use arbitrary values (`w-[350px]`) unless absolutely necessary. Use theme strings.
*   Focus rings: Use `ring-2 ring-ring ring-offset-1`. Never `ring-offset-2`.

## Code Generation Preferences
*   **Layout**: Suggest `<Stack>` and `<Grid>` components over raw Tailwind div soup.
*   **Animation**: When adding a modal or dropdown, automatically suggest wrapping in `<AnimatePresence>` and using standard motion variants. Use `whileTap: { scale: 0.98 }` for buttons.
*   **Accessibility**: Always add `aria-label` to icon-only buttons.
*   **Status indicators**: Use `variant="success"`, `variant="warning"`, `variant="info"` on Badge/Chip for status. Use `variant="soft"` for tinted badges.

## Release Workflow
*   After editing a component in `packages/ui`, remind the user to run `npx changeset` if they want to publish.
